Description: Fix CVE-2025-64459 - Prevent SQL injection in Q/QuerySet via _connector kwarg
 QuerySet.filter(), QuerySet.exclude(), QuerySet.get(), and the Q class were
 subject to SQL injection when a maliciously crafted dictionary was passed via
 dictionary expansion as the _connector keyword argument. This patch validates
 that _connector is one of the allowed connector strings (AND/OR) or None,
 raising ValueError otherwise.
 .
 Backported from upstream commit 59ae82e67053d281ff4562a24bbba21299f0a7d4
 (Django 4.2.x). Adjusted for Django 3.2.x: XOR connector does not exist
 in 3.2 (introduced in 4.1), so the connectors allowlist is (None, AND, OR).
Origin: backport, https://github.com/django/django/commit/59ae82e67053d281ff4562a24bbba21299f0a7d4
Author: Jacob Walls <jacobtylerwalls@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-12

